{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775867600225,"sessionID":"ses_2860b2284ffeKRyyLhi5s5T4BC","part":{"id":"prt_d79f519dc001M0eS0YW33I7fBB","messageID":"msg_d79f50933001q2WrViP9Q6M3RB","sessionID":"ses_2860b2284ffeKRyyLhi5s5T4BC","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_f580459cab444856b226cb49","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/code-execution/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/code-execution/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Code Execution (PicoD) — Design (from source)\n2: \n3: Derived from `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod` and `cmd/picod` in `/tmp/agentcube-ref`. Field names, types, tags, and constants match the Go definitions.\n4: \n5: ## Packages and entrypoint\n6: \n7: - **Main**: `cmd/picod/main.go` — parses flags, constructs `picod.Config`, `picod.NewServer(config)`, `server.Run()`.\n8: \n9: ## CLI flags and defaults\n10: \n11: | Flag        | Type   | Default | Usage string |\n12: |------------|--------|---------|--------------|\n13: | `-port`    | `int`  | `8080`  | `Port for the PicoD server to listen on` |\n14: | `-workspace` | `string` | `\"\"` | `Root directory for file operations (default: current working directory)` |\n15: \n16: `klog.InitFlags(nil)` is called so standard klog flags are also registered.\n17: \n18: ## Environment variables\n19: \n20: | Name | Constant | Usage |\n21: |------|----------|--------|\n22: | `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` | `PublicKeyEnvVar` | PEM-encoded PKIX public key (`PUBLIC KEY` block). Loaded in `NewServer` via `AuthManager.LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()`. If empty, invalid PEM, or not `*rsa.PublicKey`, `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv` returns an error and `NewServer` calls `klog.Fatalf` — **no serve without a valid key**. |\n23: \n24: ## Server configuration struct\n25: \n26: ```go\n27: type Config struct {\n28: \tPort      int    `json:\"port\"`\n29: \tWorkspace string `json:\"workspace\"`\n30: }\n31: ```\n32: \n33: ## Internal server fields (`Server`)\n34: \n35: - `engine *gin.Engine`\n36: - `config Config`\n37: - `authManager *AuthManager`\n38: - `startTime time.Time` — set to `time.Now()` in `NewServer`\n39: - `workspaceDir string` — absolute workspace root after `setWorkspace`\n40: \n41: ### Workspace resolution\n42: \n43: - If `config.Workspace != \"\"`: `setWorkspace(config.Workspace)` → `filepath.Abs` when possible, else fallback to provided string.\n44: - Else: `os.Getwd()` (fatal on error).\n45: \n46: ## Constants\n47: \n48: | Name | Value | File | Meaning |\n49: |------|-------|------|---------|\n50: | `TimeoutExitCode` | `124` | `execute.go` | Exit code when context deadline exceeded |\n51: | `MaxBodySize` | `32 << 20` (32 MiB) | `auth.go` | `http.MaxBytesReader` cap applied after successful JWT check |\n52: | `PublicKeyEnvVar` | `\"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"` | `auth.go` | Env var for PEM public key |\n53: | `maxFileMode` | `0777` | `files.go` | `parseFileMode` rejects modes `> 0777` (falls back to `0644`) |\n54: \n55: ### Default timeouts and modes\n56: \n57: - **Execute default timeout** (when `ExecuteRequest.Timeout == \"\"`): `60 * time.Second` (note: struct comment in source says `\"30s\"` but code uses 60s).\n58: - **Directory creation** (`MkdirAll`): `0755`\n59: - **Default file mode** (`parseFileMode` empty/invalid/too large): `0644` (octal parsed with `strconv.ParseUint(modeStr, 8, 32)`)\n60: \n61: ## Request / response structs (exact JSON tags)\n62: \n63: ### Execute\n64: \n65: ```go\n66: type ExecuteRequest struct {\n67: \tCommand    []string          `json:\"command\" binding:\"required\"`\n68: \tTimeout    string            `json:\"timeout\"`\n69: \tWorkingDir string            `json:\"working_dir\"`\n70: \tEnv        map[string]string `json:\"env\"`\n71: }\n72: \n73: type ExecuteResponse struct {\n74: \tStdout    string    `json:\"stdout\"`\n75: \tStderr    string    `json:\"stderr\"`\n76: \tExitCode  int       `json:\"exit_code\"`\n77: \tDuration  float64   `json:\"duration\"`\n78: \tStartTime time.Time `json:\"start_time\"`\n79: \tEndTime   time.Time `json:\"end_time\"`\n80: }\n81: ```\n82: \n83: - **Binding**: `c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)` on `POST /api/execute`.\n84: - **Command**: `exec.CommandContext(ctx, req.Command[0], req.Command[1:]...)`\n85: - **Stdout/Stderr**: `bytes.Buffer` assigned to `cmd.Stdout` and `cmd.Stderr`; no `cmd.Stdin` assignment.\n86: - **Exit code**: If `errors.Is(ctx.Err(), context.DeadlineExceeded)` → `TimeoutExitCode`; else if `cmd.ProcessState != nil` → `ExitCode()`; else `1` and append `err.Error()` to stderr (with newline if stderr non-empty).\n87: \n88: ### Files — upload response / JSON body\n89: \n90: ```go\n91: type FileInfo struct {\n92: \tPath     string    `json:\"path\"`\n93: \tSize     int64     `json:\"size\"`\n94: \tMode     string    `json:\"mode\"`\n95: \tModified time.Time `json:\"modified\"`\n96: }\n97: \n98: type UploadFileRequest struct {\n99: \tPath    string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n100: \tContent string `json:\"content\" binding:\"required\"`\n101: \tMode    string `json:\"mode\"`\n102: }\n103: ```\n104: \n105: - **Multipart**: `Content-Type` prefix `multipart/form-data` → `handleMultipartUpload`.\n106:   - Form: `c.PostForm(\"path\")`, `c.FormFile(\"file\")`, optional `c.PostForm(\"mode\")`.\n107: - **JSON**: `c.ShouldBindJSON` → Base64 decode `req.Content` with `base64.StdEncoding`.\n108: \n109: ### Files — listing\n110: \n111: ```go\n112: type FileEntry struct {\n113: \tName     string    `json:\"name\"`\n114: \tSize     int64     `json:\"size\"`\n115: \tModified time.Time `json:\"modified\"`\n116: \tMode     string    `json:\"mode\"`\n117: \tIsDir    bool      `json:\"is_dir\"`\n118: }\n119: \n120: type ListFilesResponse struct {\n121: \tFiles []FileEntry `json:\"files\"`\n122: }\n123: ```\n124: \n125: - **Query**: `path := c.Query(\"path\")` (required non-empty).\n126: \n127: ## HTTP error JSON shapes (Gin `gin.H`)\n128: \n129: - **Generic** (400/500): `{\"error\": string, \"code\": int}` (`code` is numeric HTTP status).\n130: - **Auth** (401): `{\"error\": string, \"code\": int, \"detail\": string}`.\n131: \n132: ## Gin setup and route registration\n133: \n134: Pattern from `NewServer`:\n135: \n136: 1. `gin.SetMode(gin.ReleaseMode)`\n137: 2. `engine := gin.New()`\n138: 3. Global: `engine.Use(gin.Logger(), gin.Recovery())`\n139: 4. `authManager.LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()` — fatal on error\n140: 5. API group:\n141: \n142: ```go\n143: api := engine.Group(\"/api\")\n144: api.Use(s.authManager.AuthMiddleware())\n145: {\n146: \tapi.POST(\"/execute\", s.ExecuteHandler)\n147: \tapi.POST(\"/files\", s.UploadFileHandler)\n148: \tapi.GET(\"/files\", s.ListFilesHandler)\n149: \tapi.GET(\"/files/*path\", s.DownloadFileHandler)\n150: }\n151: engine.GET(\"/health\", s.HealthCheckHandler)\n152: ```\n153: \n154: - **Download param**: `path := c.Param(\"path\")`; then `strings.TrimPrefix(path, \"/\")` before `sanitizePath`.\n155: \n156: ## Health response\n157: \n158: ```go\n159: c.JSON(http.StatusOK, gin.H{\n160: \t\"status\":  \"ok\",\n161: \t\"service\": \"PicoD\",\n162: \t\"version\": \"0.0.1\",\n163: \t\"uptime\":  time.Since(s.startTime).String(),\n164: })\n165: ```\n166: \n167: ## HTTP server\n168: \n169: ```go\n170: server := &http.Server{\n171: \tAddr:              fmt.Sprintf(\":%d\", s.config.Port),\n172: \tHandler:           s.engine,\n173: \tReadHeaderTimeout: 10 * time.Second,\n174: }\n175: return server.ListenAndServe()\n176: ```\n177: \n178: ## JWT middleware (`AuthManager`)\n179: \n180: ### Types\n181: \n182: ```go\n183: type AuthManager struct {\n184: \tpublicKey *rsa.PublicKey\n185: \tmutex     sync.RWMutex\n186: }\n187: ```\n188: \n189: ### Key loading (`LoadPublicKeyFromEnv`)\n190: \n191: 1. `keyData := os.Getenv(PublicKeyEnvVar)`\n192: 2. If empty → error: `environment variable %s is not set`\n193: 3. `pem.Decode([]byte(keyData))` — nil block → error `failed to decode PEM block`\n194: 4. `x509.ParsePKIXPublicKey(block.Bytes)` — on success assert `*rsa.PublicKey`\n195: \n196: ### `AuthMiddleware` behavior\n197: \n198: 1. `authHeader := c.GetHeader(\"Authorization\")`\n199: 2. If empty → 401 JSON missing header / JWT required detail\n200: 3. `parts := strings.Split(authHeader, \" \")` — require `len(parts) == 2` and `parts[0] == \"Bearer\"` else 401 invalid format (`Use Bearer <token>`)\n201: 4. `tokenString := parts[1]`\n202: 5. `jwt.Parse(tokenString, func(token *jwt.Token) (interface{}, error) { ... }, jwt.WithExpirationRequired(), jwt.WithIssuedAt(), jwt.WithLeeway(time.Minute))`\n203:    - Key func: require `token.Method` is `*jwt.SigningMethodRSA`; return `am.publicKey` (read lock)\n204: 6. If `err != nil || !token.Valid` → 401 `Invalid token` + detail with verification error\n205: 7. `c.Request.Body = http.MaxBytesReader(c.Writer, c.Request.Body, MaxBodySize)`\n206: 8. `c.Next()`\n207: \n208: **Note**: Any RSA signing method instance satisfies the type assert (e.g. RS256 in tests); HS256 is rejected.\n209: \n210: ## Path security (`sanitizePath`)\n211: \n212: Used by upload, list, download, and execute `working_dir`.\n213: \n214: 1. If `s.workspaceDir == \"\"` → error `workspace directory not initialized`\n215: 2. `resolvedWorkspace := filepath.EvalSymlinks(s.workspaceDir)`; on error fall back to `filepath.Abs` or `filepath.Clean`\n216: 3. `resolvedWorkspace = filepath.Clean(resolvedWorkspace)`\n217: 4. `cleanPath := filepath.Clean(p)`; if absolute, strip leading `os.PathSeparator` from path string\n218: 5. `fullPathCandidate := filepath.Clean(filepath.Join(resolvedWorkspace, cleanPath))`\n219: 6. `relPath, relErr := filepath.Rel(resolvedWorkspace, fullPathCandidate)` — error → access denied\n220: 7. If `strings.HasPrefix(relPath, \"..\"+separator)` or `relPath == \"..\"` → access denied\n221: 8. `resolvedFinalPath, err := filepath.EvalSymlinks(fullPathCandidate)`:\n222:    - If success: re-check `filepath.Rel` against `resolvedWorkspace` for `..` escape; pass → return `resolvedFinalPath`\n223:    - If error (e.g. path does not exist): return `fullPathCandidate` (already verified as inside workspace)\n224: \n225: **Upload/list responses** use `filepath.Rel(s.workspaceDir, safePath)` for JSON `path` on uploaded files (not `resolvedWorkspace` symlink expansion — `safePath` is the sanitized target path).\n226: \n227: ## Multipart vs JSON detection\n228: \n229: ```go\n230: contentType := c.ContentType()\n231: if strings.HasPrefix(contentType, \"multipart/form-data\") {\n232: \ts.handleMultipartUpload(c)\n233: } else {\n234: \ts.handleJSONBase64Upload(c)\n235: }\n236: ```\n237: \n238: ## File download headers (exact strings)\n239: \n240: - `Content-Description`: `File Transfer`\n241: - `Content-Transfer-Encoding`: `binary`\n242: - `Content-Disposition`: `fmt.Sprintf(\"attachment; filename=\\\"%s\\\"\", filepath.Base(safePath))`\n243: - `Content-Type`: `mime.TypeByExtension(filepath.Ext(safePath))` or `\"application/octet-stream\"`\n244: \n245: This document is sufficient to reconstruct handlers, routes, structs, and security checks without reading the repo.\n\n(End of file - total 245 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Code Execution (PicoD) — Design (from source)\n\nDerived from `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod` and `cmd/picod` in `/tmp/agentcube-ref`. Field names, types, tags, and constants match the Go definitions.\n\n## Packages and entrypoint\n\n- **Main**: `cmd/picod/main.go` — parses flags, constructs `picod.Config`, `picod.NewServer(config)`, `server.Run()`.\n\n## CLI flags and defaults\n\n| Flag        | Type   | Default | Usage string |\n|------------|--------|---------|--------------|\n| `-port`    | `int`  | `8080`  | `Port for the PicoD server to listen on` |\n| `-workspace` | `string` | `\"\"` | `Root directory for file operations (default: current working directory)` |\n\n`klog.InitFlags(nil)` is called so standard klog flags are also registered.\n\n## Environment variables\n\n| Name | Constant | Usage |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/code-execution/design.md","time":{"start":1775867600192,"end":1775867600222}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775867600228,"sessionID":"ses_2860b2284ffeKRyyLhi5s5T4BC","part":{"id":"prt_d79f51631001asyrmOI0al4VIj","messageID":"msg_d79f50933001q2WrViP9Q6M3RB","sessionID":"ses_2860b2284ffeKRyyLhi5s5T4BC","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_f61d1a0064b8494da71da0e3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the `CodeInterpreterClient` in the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`). The client provides functionality to create Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and execute code/files via the Router (data plane).\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-027\n10: - **Module**: `sdk-python`\n11: - **Language**: Python\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: - **Base Specs**: `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Background\n18: \n19: The AgentCube Python SDK requires a `CodeInterpreterClient` class that allows users to:\n20: 1. Create and manage Code Interpreter sessions through the Workload Manager (control plane)\n21: 2. Execute commands, run code, and manage files through the Router (data plane)\n22: 3. Handle session lifecycle including context manager support and proper cleanup\n23: \n24: ---\n25: \n26: ## Requirements\n27: \n28: ### AR-027-001: CodeInterpreterClient lifecycle\n29: \n30: The system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or creates a session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initializes `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n31: \n32: #### Scenario: AR-027-001-A — Context manager cleanup\n33: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager\n34: - **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n35: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes the data-plane session, deletes the control-plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n36: \n37: #### Scenario: AR-027-001-B — Data plane init failure after session create\n38: - **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n39: - **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises\n40: - **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise\n41: \n42: #### Scenario: AR-027-001-C — Router URL required\n43: - **GIVEN** neither `router_url` nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n44: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` runs\n45: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL`\n46: \n47: #### Scenario: AR-027-001-D — Constructor parameters with defaults\n48: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is instantiated with default parameters\n49: - **WHEN** the constructor runs\n50: - **THEN** it SHALL set `name=\"my-interpreter\"`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `ttl=3600`, `verbose=False`\n51: \n52: #### Scenario: AR-027-001-E — Reuse existing session_id\n53: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is instantiated with an existing `session_id`\n54: - **WHEN** initialization runs\n55: - **THEN** it SHALL skip session creation and use the provided session_id directly for data plane initialization\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ### AR-027-002: Code Interpreter operations — execute, files, stop\n60: \n61: The system SHALL expose `execute_command`, `run_code`, `write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files`, and `stop` delegating to the data plane client where applicable.\n62: \n63: #### Scenario: AR-027-002-A — Command non-zero exit\n64: - **GIVEN** `execute_command` receives a response with `exit_code != 0`\n65: - **WHEN** the response JSON is parsed\n66: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command`\n67: \n68: #### Scenario: AR-027-002-B — Python code execution path\n69: - **GIVEN** `language` is `python`, `py`, or `python3`\n70: - **WHEN** `run_code` runs\n71: - **THEN** the system SHALL write a timestamped `.py` file via `write_file` and execute `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: AR-027-002-C — Write file operation\n74: - **GIVEN** `write_file(content, remote_path)` is called\n75: - **WHEN** the request succeeds\n76: - **THEN** the file SHALL be created at the specified remote path with content base64 encoded and mode `0644`\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: AR-027-002-D — Upload file operation\n79: - **GIVEN** `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` is called\n80: - **WHEN** the file exists locally\n81: - **THEN** the file SHALL be uploaded as multipart form data to `api/files` with the session header\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: AR-027-002-E — Download file operation\n84: - **GIVEN** `download_file(remote_path, local_path)` is called\n85: - **WHEN** the remote file exists\n86: - **THEN** the file SHALL be downloaded as a stream and written to the local path\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: AR-027-002-F — List files operation\n89: - **GIVEN** `list_files(path=\".\")` is called\n90: - **WHEN** the request succeeds\n91: - **THEN** the system SHALL return the listing from `api/files` with query parameter `path`\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: AR-027-002-G — Stop operation\n94: - **GIVEN** `stop()` is called\n95: - **WHEN** the client has an active session\n96: - **THEN** the data plane session SHALL be closed and the control plane session SHALL be deleted\n97: \n98: ---\n99: \n100: ### AR-027-003: HTTP client contracts — control plane\n101: \n102: The system SHALL use `requests.Session` with connection pooling (`HTTPAdapter`) for Workload Manager calls.\n103: \n104: #### Scenario: AR-027-003-A — Create session\n105: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.create_session(name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600)`\n106: - **WHEN** the request succeeds\n107: - **THEN** the client SHALL `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body `{\"name\",\"namespace\",\"ttl\",\"metadata\"}` and return `data[\"sessionId\"]` or raise `ValueError` if absent\n108: \n109: #### Scenario: AR-027-003-B — Delete session\n110: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(session_id)`\n111: - **WHEN** the server returns 404\n112: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`; on other failures it SHALL log and return `False`\n113: \n114: #### Scenario: AR-027-003-C — Workload Manager URL and auth\n115: - **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url` and `auth_token` may be omitted\n116: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n117: - **THEN** `base_url` SHALL resolve from `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; token SHALL resolve from `auth_token` or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` via `read_token_from_file`, and if present set `Authorization: Bearer {token}`\n118: \n119: ---\n120: \n121: ### AR-027-004: HTTP client contracts — data plane (Code Interpreter)\n122: \n123: The system SHALL target Router-relative paths under `{base_url}` derived from `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{ns}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")` unless `base_url` is passed explicitly.\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: AR-027-004-A — Data plane base URL construction\n126: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed with `router_url`, `namespace`, and `cr_name`\n127: - **WHEN** `base_url` is not provided\n128: - **THEN** the base URL SHALL be constructed as `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")`\n129: \n130: #### Scenario: AR-027-004-B — Execute command\n131: - **WHEN** `execute_command` posts to `api/execute`\n132: - **THEN** the body SHALL be JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` and read timeout SHALL be `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds when numeric (to avoid `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124)\n133: \n134: #### Scenario: AR-027-004-C — Write file via data plane\n135: - **WHEN** `write_file` runs\n136: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST api/files` with base64 `content`, `path`, `mode` `\"0644\"`\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: AR-027-004-D — Upload file via data plane\n139: - **WHEN** `upload_file` runs\n140: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST` multipart to `api/files` with headers including `x-agentcube-session-id`\n141: \n142: #### Scenario: AR-027-004-E — Download file via data plane\n143: - **WHEN** `download_file` runs\n144: - **THEN** it SHALL `GET api/files/{clean_path}` with `stream=True` where `clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`\n145: \n146: #### Scenario: AR-027-004-F — List files via data plane\n147: - **WHEN** `list_files` runs\n148: - **THEN** it SHALL `GET api/files` with query parameter `path`\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ### AR-027-005: Session header management\n153: \n154: The system SHALL use lowercase header name `x-agentcube-session-id` for SDK Router requests.\n155: \n156: #### Scenario: AR-027-005-A — Code Interpreter session header\n157: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed\n158: - **WHEN** any `_request` or upload runs\n159: - **THEN** the session SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` (upload sets it explicitly on the multipart POST)\n160: \n161: ---\n162: \n163: ### AR-027-006: Exception hierarchy\n164: \n165: The system SHALL define `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError` in `agentcube.exceptions`.\n166: \n167: #### Scenario: AR-027-006-A — Command failure\n168: - **GIVEN** remote command returns non-zero exit code in JSON\n169: - **WHEN** `execute_command` processes the response\n170: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n171: \n172: #### Scenario: AR-027-006-B — Session error definition\n173: - **GIVEN** `SessionError` is defined in `agentcube.exceptions`\n174: - **WHEN** a session operation fails\n175: - **THEN** `SessionError` MAY be raised by the client\n176: \n177: #### Scenario: AR-027-006-C — Data plane error definition\n178: - **GIVEN** `DataPlaneError` is defined in `agentcube.exceptions`\n179: - **WHEN** a data plane operation fails\n180: - **THEN** `DataPlaneError` MAY be raised by the client\n181: \n182: ---\n183: \n184: ### AR-027-007: Timeout behavior\n185: \n186: The system SHALL default control-plane and data-plane read timeouts to `120` seconds and connect timeout to `5.0` seconds unless overridden per call.\n187: \n188: #### Scenario: AR-027-007-A — Per-call override for code execution\n189: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(command, timeout=None)`\n190: - **WHEN** `timeout` is `None`\n191: - **THEN** the effective timeout value SHALL default to `self.timeout` (`120`) for constructing the PicoD timeout string and read-timeout buffer logic\n192: \n193: #### Scenario: AR-027-007-B — Connection pool configuration\n194: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` or `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed\n195: - **WHEN** no pool settings are provided\n196: - **THEN** the defaults SHALL be `pool_connections=10` and `pool_maxsize=10`\n197: \n198: ---\n199: \n200: ### AR-027-008: Public API surface\n201: \n202: The system SHALL export the `CodeInterpreterClient` from the root package.\n203: \n204: #### Scenario: AR-027-008-A — Root package exports\n205: - **GIVEN** `agentcube/__init__.py` is imported\n206: - **WHEN** `__all__` is accessed\n207: - **THEN** it SHALL contain `[\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]`\n208: \n209: #### Scenario: AR-027-008-B — Clients submodule exports\n210: - **GIVEN** `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` is imported\n211: - **WHEN** `__all__` is accessed\n212: - **THEN** it SHALL contain `[\"ControlPlaneClient\", \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\", \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"]`\n213: \n214: ---\n215: \n216: ## Acceptance Criteria\n217: \n218: - [ ] AC001: CodeInterpreterClient constructs with proper defaults (name, namespace, ttl, verbose)\n219: - [ ] AC002: CodeInterpreterClient creates session via ControlPlaneClient when session_id not provided\n220: - [ ] AC003: CodeInterpreterClient supports context manager protocol with proper cleanup\n221: - [ ] AC004: CodeInterpreterClient handles data plane init failure with session cleanup\n222: - [ ] AC005: CodeInterpreterClient raises ValueError when router_url is missing\n223: - [ ] AC006: execute_command raises CommandExecutionError on non-zero exit code\n224: - [ ] AC007: run_code supports python/py/python3 languages with timestamped file execution\n225: - [ ] AC008: write_file creates remote files with base64 content and mode 0644\n226: - [ ] AC009: upload_file uploads files via multipart to data plane\n227: - [ ] AC010: download_file downloads files as streams to local path\n228: - [ ] AC011: list_files returns file listing from data plane\n229: - [ ] AC012: stop closes data plane and deletes control plane session\n230: - [ ] AC013: ControlPlaneClient.create_session returns sessionId from response\n231: - [ ] AC014: ControlPlaneClient.delete_session returns True on 404\n232: - [ ] AC015: ControlPlaneClient resolves base_url and auth from env/args\n233: - [ ] AC016: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient constructs base_url from router components\n234: - [ ] AC017: Session header x-agentcube-session-id is set on all data plane requests\n235: - [ ] AC018: Exception hierarchy includes AgentCubeError, CommandExecutionError, SessionError, DataPlaneError\n236: - [ ] AC019: Default timeouts are 120s read, 5.0s connect\n237: - [ ] AC020: Connection pool defaults are 10 connections, 10 max size\n238: \n239: ---\n240: \n241: ## Architecture Notes\n242: \n243: ### Package Layout\n244: \n245: | Path | Role |\n246: |------|------|\n247: | `pyproject.toml` | Package `agentcube-sdk`, dependencies |\n248: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports |\n249: | `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` |\n250: | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | `ControlPlaneClient` |\n251: | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` |\n252: | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception classes |\n253: | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` |\n254: | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file` |\n255: | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger` |\n256: \n257: ### Key Components\n258: \n259: | Component | Description |\n260: |-----------|-------------|\n261: | `CodeInterpreterClient` | Main client for Code Interpreter sessions |\n262: | `ControlPlaneClient` | Handles Workload Manager API calls |\n263: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | Handles Router data plane API calls |\n264: | `AgentCubeError` | Base exception class |\n265: | `CommandExecutionError` | Raised on command non-zero exit |\n266: | `SessionError` | Raised on session operations failure |\n267: | `DataPlaneError` | Raised on data plane operations failure |\n268: \n269: ### Configuration Resolution\n270: \n271: | Component | Resolved settings |\n272: |-----------|-------------------|\n273: | `ControlPlaneClient` | `base_url` ← `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; `Authorization` ← `auth_token` or SA token file; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10` |\n274: | `CodeInterpreterClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL` (required); `workload_manager_url` / `auth_token` passed to `ControlPlaneClient` |\n275: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`; `base_url` from `base_url` **or** `router_url`+`namespace`+`cr_name` |\n276: \n277: ---\n278: \n279: ## References\n280: \n281: - Base design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n282: - Base spec: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n283: - Package root: `agentcube/`\n284: - Source location: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/`\n\n(End of file - total 284 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the `CodeInterpreterClient` in the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`). The client provides functionality to create Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and execute code/files via the Router (data plane).\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-027\n- **Module**: `sdk-python`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Base Specs**: `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe AgentCube Python SDK requires a `CodeInterpreterClient` class that allows users to:\n1. Create and manage Code Interpreter sessions through the Workload Manager (control plane)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775867600189,"end":1775867600225}}}}
