{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775867614105,"sessionID":"ses_2860b2284ffeKRyyLhi5s5T4BC","part":{"id":"prt_d79f54fc5001GUy4EIiLF3Lq7Q","messageID":"msg_d79f53913001p5HIuHHRZHVQXk","sessionID":"ses_2860b2284ffeKRyyLhi5s5T4BC","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_0a254f6b964643c3a890ac47","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-026/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-026/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** cmd/cli  \n4: **Language:** Python  \n5: **Size:** M  \n6: **Stage:** ST-3 (Design Complete - Implementation Pending)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Implementation Tasks\n11: \n12: ### Phase 1: Provider Selection & Prerequisites (T001-T004)\n13: \n14: - [ ] **T001** Implement `--provider` option in `publish` command (default: `agentcube`)\n15:   - *File:* `agentcube/cli/main.py:311-315`\n16:   - *Verify:* `publish --provider agentcube` uses AgentRuntime CR, `publish --provider k8s` uses Deployment+Service\n17:   - *Test:* Run publish with both providers and verify correct route taken\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T002** Validate `router_url` prerequisite for agentcube provider\n20:   - *File:* `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py:293-296`\n21:   - *Verify:* ValueError raised when `router_url` missing in metadata\n22:   - *Test:* Publish with agentcube provider without router_url\n23: \n24: - [ ] **T003** Validate `workload_manager_url` prerequisite for agentcube provider  \n25:   - *File:* `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py:293-296`\n26:   - *Verify:* ValueError raised when `workload_manager_url` missing in metadata\n27:   - *Test:* Publish with agentcube provider without workload_manager_url\n28: \n29: - [ ] **T004** Implement k8s provider options: `--node-port`, `--replicas`, `--namespace`\n30:   - *File:* `agentcube/cli/main.py:316-330`\n31:   - *Verify:* Options passed to `PublishRuntime.publish()` correctly\n32:   - *Test:* Verify NodePort range (30000-32767) validation\n33: \n34: ---\n35: \n36: ### Phase 2: Kubernetes Provider Deployment (T005-T009)\n37: \n38: - [ ] **T005** Implement `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` creating Deployment + NodePort Service\n39:   - *File:* `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py:64-172`\n40:   - *Verify:* Returns deployment_name, service_name, namespace, replicas, container_port, node_port, service_url\n41:   - *Test:* Deploy and verify K8s resources created\n42: \n43: - [ ] **T006** Implement `wait_for_deployment_ready` with 120s timeout\n44:   - *File:* `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py:174-209`\n45:   - *Verify:* Polls until replicas ready or raises TimeoutError\n46:   - *Test:* Verify timeout raises ValueError after 120s\n47: \n48: - [ ] **T007** Implement `--node-port` specification (30000-32767)\n49:   - *File:* `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py:89-90`\n50:   - *Verify:* NodePort must be in valid range\n51:   - *Test:* Publish with invalid node-port should fail\n52: \n53: - [ ] **T008** Implement `--replicas` specification\n54:   - *File:* `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py:115`\n55:   - *Verify:* Deployment uses specified replica count\n56:   - *Test:* `publish --provider k8s --replicas 3` creates 3 replicas\n57: \n58: - [ ] **T009** Implement `--namespace` specification\n59:   - *File:* `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py:26`\n60:   - *Verify:* Resources created in specified namespace\n61:   - *Test:* `publish --provider k8s --namespace myns` creates resources in `myns`\n62: \n63: - [ ] **T010** Implement `KubernetesProvider.delete_agent` with 404 handling\n64:   - *File:* `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py:251-295`\n65:   - *Verify:* Returns status: \"deleted\", ignores 404 errors\n66:   - *Test:* Delete non-existent agent should not raise error\n67: \n68: ---\n69: \n70: ### Phase 3: AgentCube Provider Deployment (T011-T014)\n71: \n72: - [ ] **T011** Implement `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` with AgentRuntime CR\n73:   - *File:* `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py:68-177`\n74:   - *Verify:* Creates CR with WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL, ROUTER_URL, sessionTimeout: \"15m\", maxSessionDuration: \"8h\", imagePullSecrets\n75:   - *Test:* Deploy and verify CR created with correct spec\n76: \n77: - [ ] **T012** Verify AgentRuntime CR API group/version: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n78:   - *File:* `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py:12-14`\n79:   - *Verify:* CR uses correct group, version, plural\n80:   - *Test:* Verify CRD exists in cluster\n81: \n82: - [ ] **T013** Add `imagePullSecrets` to AgentRuntime: `[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n83:   - *File:* `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py:111-145`\n84:   - *Verify:* Spec includes imagePullSecrets\n85:   - *Test:* Verify in deployed CR\n86: \n87: - [ ] **T014** Implement AgentRuntime readiness probe fields from metadata\n88:   - *File:* `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py:77-78`\n89:   - *Verify:* readiness_probe_path and readiness_probe_port used\n90:   - *Test:* Deploy with probe config verified\n91: \n92: ---\n93: \n94: ### Phase 4: Invoke Command Routing (T015-T017)\n95: \n96: - [ ] **T015** Route invoke to AgentRuntime endpoint for agentcube provider\n97:   - *File:* `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py:41-75`\n98:   - *Verify:* URL rewritten to `/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n99:   - *Test:* Invoke with agentcube provider uses correct path\n100: \n101: - [ ] **T016** Route invoke to direct service endpoint for k8s provider\n102:   - *File:* `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py:118-140`\n103:   - *Verify:* POST directly to service endpoint from metadata\n104:   - *Test:* Invoke with k8s provider uses direct endpoint\n105: \n106: - [ ] **T017** Add `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` header when session_id in metadata\n107:   - *File:* `